SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 43, Chapter 1, Part 6, is amended by
deleting the part and substituting the following:
43-1-601. Creation.
There is created and established the Tennessee agriculture and forestry hall of
fame, governed as provided by this part. It is the intent of the general assembly that the
Tennessee agriculture and forestry hall of fame be the successor to, and a continuation
of, the Tennessee agricultural hall of fame, established by Chapter 43 of the Public Acts
of 1937.
43-1-602. Board — Members.
(a) There is established the Tennessee agriculture and forestry hall of fame
board by transfer and expansion of the duties and responsibilities of the Tennessee
agricultural hall of fame board. The board consists of nine (9) members.
(b) Effective July 1, 2025, the existing membership of the Tennessee agricultural
hall of fame board is vacated and reconstituted as the Tennessee agriculture and
forestry hall of fame board, with the members of the board to be appointed as follows:
(1) The commissioner of agriculture or the commissioner's designee;
(2) The senior vice chancellor of the University of Tennessee Institute of
Agriculture;
(3) The dean of Tennessee State University College of Agriculture;
(4) The president of the Tennessee Farm Bureau Federation;
