(5) The Tennessee FFA State Director;
(6) One (1) member from the middle grand division appointed by the
speaker of the house of representatives;
(7) One (1) member from the eastern grand division appointed by the
speaker of the senate;
(8) One (1) member from the western grand division appointed by the
governor; and
(9) One (1) member from the state at-large appointed by the governor.
(c) The persons appointed under subdivisions (b)(6)–(9) shall demonstrate
significant ties to agriculture or forestry in this state by engagement in agricultural or
forestry business, science, or engineering or by employment or service with an entity
that serves the conservation of natural resources or betterment of farming or forestry
interests.
(d) To stagger the terms of the newly appointed board members, the appointing
authorities shall make initial appointments as follows:
(1) The person appointed under subdivision (b)(6) is appointed for a term
of six (6) years, which expires on June 30, 2031;
(2) The person appointed under subdivision (b)(7) is appointed for a term
of four (4) years, which expires on June 30, 2029; and
(3) The persons appointed under subdivisions (b)(8) and (9) are
appointed for terms of two (2) years, which expire on June 30, 2027.
(e) Members serving on the Tennessee agricultural hall of fame board as of
June 30, 2025, may be reappointed to serve as members of the Tennessee agriculture
and forestry hall of fame board after such date.
(f)
